This paper deals with generating adversarial examples for autonomous driving systems using deep neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for generating physical-world-resilient adversarial examples, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The paper also involves the evaluation of the generated adversarial examples in real-world scenarios, which falls under robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with the security aspect of autonomous driving systems, which falls under cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
